<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD INSTALLATION -
        VALVE LEVER INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="6">
        <title>VALVE LEVER INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install valve lever (rocker arm) assembly onto the cylinder head using six (6) cylinder
                    head mounting bolts as follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Insert the rocker arm and shaft assembly with the long cylinder head bolts into
                        their respective bolt holes. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050460">4.60</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">the long cylinder head bolts in fingertight (except the two end bolts). Place a
                        0.005 in. (0.013mm) feeler gauge between the outside brackets and the rocker levers to prevent
                        binding. Finger-tighten the remaining two end bolts. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050461">4.61</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the cylinder head bolts in three stages as specified under "
                    <emph type="bold">SPECIAL TORQUE VALUES</emph>" in this section.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Check the two end rocker arms for freedom of movement after tightening the cylinder head
                            bolts.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two 0.005 in. (0.013mm) feeler gauges.</para>
                <figure id="ef1050459" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2315" filename="../figeg2/eg2315.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.59.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Push Rod</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Cylinder Head</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050460" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2324" filename="../figeg2/eg2324.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.60.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Rocker Shaft Bracket</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Cylinder Head</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050461" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2446" filename="../figeg2/eg2446.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.61.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Bracket</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Feeler Gauge</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Wrench</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Rocker lever</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust valve lash as follows:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>All valves are adjusted by rotating the engine only twice.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft until the #1 piston is on the compression stroke and the
                        timing pointer on the front cover is in line with the TDC mark on the vibration damper.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Confirm that the #1 piston is on the compression stroke by turning both push rods by
                                hand to verify that both valves are closed. The valves are closed when the push rods are
                                loose and can be turned easily.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Set valve lash by loosening the lock nut and turning the valve adjustment screw with
                        the appropriate size feeler gauge inserted between the rocker arm and valve stem tip. Tighten
                        the valve adjustment screw until the valve lever can support the feeler gauge. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050462">4.62</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        and "
                        <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>" for valve lash.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the lock nut once the valve adjustment is set. Remove the feeler gauge.
                        Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050463">4.63</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install baffle assembly. Be sure that deflectors are securely attached to baffle. If
                    necessary replace deflector using multi-purpose adhesive sealant.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050462" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg15234" filename="../figcg1/cg15234.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.62.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050463" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg15233" filename="../figcg1/cg15233.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.63.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Valve Lash Adjustment Sequence</title>
            <para>Six valves are adjusted when the #1 piston is at TDC (compression) and the remaining six are adjusted
                when the #6 piston is at TDC (compression). Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050464">Figure 4.64</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050464" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg15236" filename="../figcg1/cg15236.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.64.</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
